### Milestone 11 — Signed-offset payload encoding (v6 stream) ✓

The current absolute-index payload places ratio=1.0 at index 2^29 (centre of
the 30-bit log-space range). A smooth step of ratio=1.0001 produces absolute
index ~536,889,320 — requiring 30 bits even though the deviation from identity
is tiny. Nearly all u32 payloads on smooth data cluster near 2^29.

The fix (v6): ClassNormal (u16) now stores a signed int16 offset from log-space
centre at 30-bit precision; ClassNormal32 (u32) stores int32 offset for larger
deviations. The 7-symbol rANS alphabet is unchanged. Ratios within ±0.01% of
identity have offset < int16Max=32767 and take 2 bytes instead of 4.

Results from TestSignedOffsetSavings (n=50,000):
  NearConstant / Float32Smooth: 50% payload savings (all → u16)
  Volatile:                     42% payload savings
  Sensor:                        4% payload savings (larger deviations)
  NeuralWeight:                  ~0% (weights span many octaves → u32 dominates)
TestU24Savings results unchanged (measures quantized mode, not v6 adaptive).
All three tolerances (ε=1e-3, 1e-6, 1e-9) give identical sizes at ε≤1e-6
(delta30≈1.49e-8 < 1e-6 → fastPath; precision decoupled from tolerance in v6).

