**12b — Adaptive precision-relative tiers (v7 stream)**
Both v5 and v6 fail to connect the precision you request to the tier you land in.

  v5 regression: `PrecisionBits` clamped to 16. Requesting 6 sig figs (B=20)
  silently becomes B=16; 16-bit relErr > tight tolerance → spills to u32 (4B,
  30-bit). Every precision request above 5 sig figs pays 4 bytes.

  v6 regression: 30-bit hardcoded for everything. `PrecisionBits` ignored.
  Offset encoding improved smooth-data bytes, but the configured precision
  has no effect on which tier is used.

  v7 fix: offset computed at `opts.PrecisionBits`. Tier set by `|off|` magnitude.

  Precision → dominant tier mapping in v7:
    N=4–5sf  B=13–19  max offset ≤ ±256K  → u16 (2B)  [smooth data → u8]
    N=6–7sf  B=20–23  max offset ≤ ±4M    → u24 (3B)  ← fills the gap
    N=8–9sf  B=26–30  max offset ≤ ±537M  → u32 (4B)

  Smooth data at any precision: offset ≈ small → u8 regardless of B.
  The u24 tier is the natural home for 6–7 sig fig requests; without it those
