### SIMD / intrinsics — uniform-stride throughput variant  [effort: L]
SIMD requires a branch-free, uniform-stride payload loop. The v5 adaptive
stream is fundamentally incompatible with this: per-ratio tier selection
(u16/u32/f64) means stride varies by ratio. These two designs cannot share
a hot path — SIMD requires a separate encoder/decoder pair.

Proposed separation:
  .tzrz   — current adaptive path (v1–v5); minimum bytes, mixed stride
  .tzrzU  — SIMD uniform path; user picks one tier at encode time (u16 or
            u32); decoder keyed on extension; no adaptive selection
 — retest after M11]
