### Delta coding of quantized index stream  [effort: L]
Before rANS, encode the delta between adjacent class symbols rather than
the raw symbols. For smooth data Δ≈0 dominates, giving a more skewed
distribution and higher rANS compression. Zero benefit for volatile/random
data. Requires a new stream version.
Gate on: prototype delta transform showing ≥5% ratio improvement on
at least two dataset classes in the existing harness.

### Context-adaptive rANS  [effort: L]
Maintain per-context frequency tables (keyed on previous class symbol)
instead of one global table. Each per-context distribution has lower
entropy than the global one. Header grows by one table per context.
Meaningful gain only when class transitions are structured.
Gate on: entropy analysis showing per-context entropy materially lower
than global entropy on target datasets.

### v6 — Predictive-residual lossless stream  [effort: L]
A predictor (last ratio or linear extrapolation) + entropy-coded residual
could achieve genuinely lossless compression better than v2's ~1.0 ratio.
Key risk: ratios are already a first-difference transform on values; a
second differencing layer may yield little in practice.
Gate on: prototype residual coder showing lossless ratio < 0.90 on
Smooth/Sensor dataset (current lossless is ~1.0007 — near-zero gain).
